dev/adr/ADR-0.6.0-error-taxonomy.md:101:**B — Per-module errors only; no top-level wrap.** Cleanest module boundaries. The real cost is not "mapping table size" — it is that bindings have no single entry-point type to dispatch on; every public function would return a different error type, multiplying binding-side type machinery (PyO3 `IntoPy` impls, napi-rs `From<E> for napi::Error` impls) per module. Rejected on entry-point-count grounds, not mapping-burden grounds.
