dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z.log:132:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013ZAKEi34ZLjwKxv79bEYtV","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: Python Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-04-24\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public Python surface for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/python/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# Python Interface\n11\t\n12\tThis file owns Python-visible symbol spelling and attribute casing.\n13\tCross-binding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n14\t\n15\t## Runtime surface\n16\t\n17\tThe canonical runtime verbs available to Python callers are:\n18\t\n19\t- `Engine.open(...)`\n20\t- `engine.write(...)`\n21\t- `engine.search(...)`\n22\t- `engine.close()`\n23\t- `admin.configure(...)`\n24\t\n25\t`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\n26\towned by `design/engine.md`.\n27\t\n28\t> **0.6.0 caveat (2026-05-17, Phase 12-TX).** The PyO3 binding currently\n29\t> returns the engine handle only; the structured open report is dropped.\n30\t> Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report:\n31\t> OpenReport }` and the report is populated, but binding-side surfacing\n32\t> defers to 0.6.1 (slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT). Clients that need\n33\t> migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage\n34\t> data wait for 0.6.1.\n35\t\n36\t`Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` accepts the\n37\tengine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in snake_case:\n38\t\n39\t- `embedder_pool_size`\n40\t- `scheduler_runtime_threads`\n41\t- `provenance_row_cap`\n42\t- `embedder_call_timeout_ms`\n43\t- `slow_threshold_ms`\n44\t\n45\tThe keyword form and `EngineConfig` object form are equivalent. Python\n46\texecutor usage remains caller-owned and is not an engine config field.\n47\t\n48\t## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n49\t\n50\tThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n51\t\n52\t- `engine.drain(timeout_s=...)`\n53\t- `engine.counters()`\n54\t- `engine.set_profiling(enabled=...)`\n55\t- `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(value=...)`\n56\t\n57\tSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n58\t\n59\t- `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`\n60\t\n61\tThe helper maps engine events into Python `logging.LogRecord`s with the stable\n62\t`fathomdb` payload described by `design/bindings.md`.\n63\t\n64\t## Caller-visible data shapes\n65\t\n66\t- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n67\t- `SearchResult.projection_cursor`\n68\t- `SearchResult.soft_fallback.branch`\n69\t\n70\t`soft_fallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n71\t\n72\t## Errors\n73\t\n74\tPython exposes one catch-all base class plus one concrete subclass per canonical\n75\trow in `design/errors.md`.\n76\t\n77\tExamples of caller-visible subclasses:\n78\t\n79\t- `DatabaseLockedError`\n80\t- `CorruptionError`\n81\t- `MigrationError`\n82\t- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n83\t- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n84\t- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n85\t- `SchemaValidationError`\n86\t- `OverloadedError`\n87\t- `ClosingError`\n88\t\n89\tPayload fields remain typed attributes; callers do not dispatch on message\n90\ttext.\n91\t\n92\t## Non-presence\n93\t\n94\tPython does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\n95\tthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `check-integrity`, `--quick`,\n96\t`--full`, or `--round-trip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n97\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"5f49aef5-5cea-406d-8e6f-004a8be18267","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:21.070Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/dev/interfaces/python.md","content":"---\ntitle: Python Public Interface\ndate: 2026-04-24\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public Python surface for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/python/; design/bindings.md; design/errors.md; design/lifecycle.md; design/engine.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# Python Interface\n\nThis file owns Python-visible symbol spelling and attribute casing.\nCross-binding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Runtime surface\n\nThe canonical runtime verbs available to Python callers are:\n\n- `Engine.open(...)`\n- `engine.write(...)`\n- `engine.search(...)`\n- `engine.close()`\n- `admin.configure(...)`\n\n`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report\nowned by `design/engine.md`.\n\n> **0.6.0 caveat (2026-05-17, Phase 12-TX).** The PyO3 binding currently\n> returns the engine handle only; the structured open report is dropped.\n> Native Rust `Engine::open` returns `OpenedEngine { engine, report:\n> OpenReport }` and the report is populated, but binding-side surfacing\n> defers to 0.6.1 (slice 12-TX-OPENREPORT). Clients that need\n> migration-version-reached / embedder-identity-confirmed / open-stage\n> data wait for 0.6.1.\n\n`Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` accepts the\nengine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in snake_case:\n\n- `embedder_pool_size`\n- `scheduler_runtime_threads`\n- `provenance_row_cap`\n- `embedder_call_timeout_ms`\n- `slow_threshold_ms`\n\nThe keyword form and `EngineConfig` object form are equivalent. Python\nexecutor usage remains caller-owned and is not an engine config field.\n\n## Engine-attached instrumentation / control\n\nThese are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:\n\n- `engine.drain(timeout_s=...)`\n- `engine.counters()`\n- `engine.set_profiling(enabled=...)`\n- `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(value=...)`\n\nSubscriber attachment is provided by:\n\n- `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`\n\nThe helper maps engine events into Python `logging.LogRecord`s with the stable\n`fathomdb` payload described by `design/bindings.md`.\n\n## Caller-visible data shapes\n\n- `WriteReceipt.cursor`\n- `SearchResult.projection_cursor`\n- `SearchResult.soft_fallback.branch`\n\n`soft_fallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.\n\n## Errors\n\nPython exposes one catch-all base class plus one concrete subclass per canonical\nrow in `design/errors.md`.\n\nExamples of caller-visible subclasses:\n\n- `DatabaseLockedError`\n- `CorruptionError`\n- `MigrationError`\n- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`\n- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`\n- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`\n- `SchemaValidationError`\n- `OverloadedError`\n- `ClosingError`\n\nPayload fields remain typed attributes; callers do not dispatch on message\ntext.\n\n## Non-presence\n\nPython does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,\nthere is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `check-integrity`, `--quick`,\n`--full`, or `--round-trip`. See `design/recovery.md`.\n","numLines":97,"startLine":1,"totalLines":97}}}
dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z.log:174:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016m38pfz5gBMyzKe34HSPBE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: CLI Public Interface\n3\tdate: 2026-05-12\n4\ttarget_release: 0.6.0\n5\tdesc: Public CLI surface for 0.6.0\n6\tblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/lib.rs; design/recovery.md; design/errors.md\n7\tstatus: locked\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t# CLI Interface\n11\t\n12\tPublic CLI surface for the 0.6.0 operator binary. The canonical verb table and\n13\trecovery semantics are owned by `design/recovery.md`; this file owns concrete\n14\tflag spelling, root command paths, and exit-code classes.\n15\t\n16\t## Roots\n17\t\n18\t- `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss <sub-flag>...`\n19\t- `fathomdb doctor <verb> ...`\n20\t\n21\tThe CLI is **operator-only** in 0.6.0. It does not mirror the SDK five-verb\n22\tapplication surface and does not ship `search` / `get` / `list` query verbs.\n23\t\n24\t## Output posture\n25\t\n26\t- `--json` is the normative machine-readable contract on every verb.\n27\t- `doctor check-integrity` emits a single JSON object.\n28\t- `doctor check-integrity --full` may emit doctor-only finding codes such as\n29\t  `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`.\n30\t- `recover` JSON output is a progress stream plus summary, owned by\n31\t  `design/recovery.md`.\n32\t- `--pretty` is a human-only formatter on verbs that explicitly document it;\n33\t  it is not a separate machine schema.\n34\t\n35\t## Exit-code classes\n36\t\n37\t| Code | Stable meaning                                                       | Primary owner                    |\n38\t| ---- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |\n39\t| `0`  | successful completion with no findings that require a non-zero exit  | this file                        |\n40\t| `64` | recovery completed only because lossy action was explicitly accepted | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n41\t| `65` | doctor/verification surface found actionable non-clean state         | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n42\t| `66` | export/materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb  | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n43\t| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        | this file                        |\n44\t| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 | this file + `design/bindings.md` |\n45\t\n46\t## Doctor verbs\n47\t\n48\t| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit class                          |\n49\t| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n50\t| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65 / 70 / 71 |\n51\t| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `doctor-export-*` = 0 / 66 / 71     |\n52\t| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65           |\n53\t| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n54\t| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n55\t| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n56\t| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n57\t\n58\t`doctor-check-*` means the verb may use the exit-code class set `{0, 65, 70,\n59\t71}` depending on clean/findings/unrecoverable/lock-held outcome.\n60\t\n61\t## Recover root\n62\t\n63\t`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n64\t\n65\t```text\n66\tfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n67\t  [--truncate-wal]\n68\t  [--rebuild-vec0]\n69\t  [--rebuild-projections]\n70\t  [--excise-source <id>]\n71\t```\n72\t\n73\tExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n74\t\n75\t`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\n76\treject it as unknown.\n77\t\n78\t`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\n79\tor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\n80\tbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n81\t\n82\t## Error to exit-code mapping\n83\t\n84\tThe CLI dispatcher translates engine error variants (and CLI-detected\n85\tpreconditions) to the exit-code classes above. This table binds each variant\n86\tto its class.\n87\t\n88\t| Source error variant                             | Exit code | Class         |\n89\t| ------------------------------------------------ | --------- | ------------- |\n90\t| (clean completion)                               | 0         | success       |\n91\t| recover sub-action gated by `--accept-data-loss` | 64        | data-loss-ack |\n92\t| `doctor check-integrity` findings non-empty      | 65        | findings      |\n93\t| `doctor safe-export` failed manifest/export step | 66        | artifact-fail |\n94\t| `EngineError::Storage`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n95\t| `EngineError::Projection`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n96\t| `EngineError::Vector`                            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n97\t| `EngineError::Embedder`                          | 70        | unrecoverable |\n98\t| `EngineError::Scheduler`                         | 70        | unrecoverable |\n99\t| `EngineError::OpStore`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n100\t| `EngineError::Overloaded`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n101\t| `EngineError::SchemaValidation`                  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n102\t| `EngineError::WriteValidation`                   | 70        | unrecoverable |\n103\t| `EngineError::EmbedderNotConfigured`             | 70        | unrecoverable |\n104\t| `EngineError::KindNotVectorIndexed`              | 70        | unrecoverable |\n105\t| `EngineError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}`     | 70        | unrecoverable |\n106\t| `EngineOpenError::DatabaseLocked{..}`            | 71        | lock-held     |\n107\t| `EngineError::Closing`                           | 71        | lock-held     |\n108\t| `EngineOpenError::Corruption(..)`                | 70        | unrecoverable |\n109\t| `EngineOpenError::IncompatibleSchemaVersion{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n110\t| `EngineOpenError::MigrationError{..}`            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n111\t| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderIdentityMismatch{..}`  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n112\t| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n113\t| `EngineOpenError::Io{..}`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n114\t\n115\t## JSON output wrapping\n116\t\n117\t`fathomdb-cli` owns top-level discriminator wrapping. The engine returns\n118\ttyped report structs; the CLI serializes them under a `verb` discriminator.\n119\t\n120\t- All `--json` output is one JSON object (or an NDJSON stream for `recover`).\n121\t- Doctor verb wrapping pattern: `{ \"verb\": \"<verb-name>\", ...flattened_engine_report_fields... }`.\n122\t- Non-flat reports nest naturally. For example, `IntegrityReport` serializes\n123\t  as `{ \"verb\": \"check-integrity\", \"physical\": {...}, \"logical\": {...}, \"semantic\": {...} }`.\n124\t- Field name policy: serde default `snake_case`. Any divergence from engine\n125\t  field spellings lives in the CLI serialization layer; the engine report\n126\t  structs are not renamed to satisfy CLI spelling requirements.\n127\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"c6c589a6-9dfd-4784-b34b-2b2d95eea8fd","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:29.551Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z/dev/interfaces/cli.md","content":"---\ntitle: CLI Public Interface\ndate: 2026-05-12\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Public CLI surface for 0.6.0\nblast_radius: src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/lib.rs; design/recovery.md; design/errors.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# CLI Interface\n\nPublic CLI surface for the 0.6.0 operator binary. The canonical verb table and\nrecovery semantics are owned by `design/recovery.md`; this file owns concrete\nflag spelling, root command paths, and exit-code classes.\n\n## Roots\n\n- `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss <sub-flag>...`\n- `fathomdb doctor <verb> ...`\n\nThe CLI is **operator-only** in 0.6.0. It does not mirror the SDK five-verb\napplication surface and does not ship `search` / `get` / `list` query verbs.\n\n## Output posture\n\n- `--json` is the normative machine-readable contract on every verb.\n- `doctor check-integrity` emits a single JSON object.\n- `doctor check-integrity --full` may emit doctor-only finding codes such as\n  `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`.\n- `recover` JSON output is a progress stream plus summary, owned by\n  `design/recovery.md`.\n- `--pretty` is a human-only formatter on verbs that explicitly document it;\n  it is not a separate machine schema.\n\n## Exit-code classes\n\n| Code | Stable meaning                                                       | Primary owner                    |\n| ---- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |\n| `0`  | successful completion with no findings that require a non-zero exit  | this file                        |\n| `64` | recovery completed only because lossy action was explicitly accepted | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `65` | doctor/verification surface found actionable non-clean state         | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `66` | export/materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb  | this file + `design/recovery.md` |\n| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        | this file                        |\n| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 | this file + `design/bindings.md` |\n\n## Doctor verbs\n\n| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit class                          |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |\n| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65 / 70 / 71 |\n| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `doctor-export-*` = 0 / 66 / 71     |\n| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65           |\n| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `doctor-check-*`                    |\n\n`doctor-check-*` means the verb may use the exit-code class set `{0, 65, 70,\n71}` depending on clean/findings/unrecoverable/lock-held outcome.\n\n## Recover root\n\n`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.\n\n```text\nfathomdb recover --accept-data-loss\n  [--truncate-wal]\n  [--rebuild-vec0]\n  [--rebuild-projections]\n  [--excise-source <id>]\n```\n\nExit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.\n\n`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs\nreject it as unknown.\n\n`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed\nor stale projections. The docs may refer to \"regenerate\" as the workflow name,\nbut there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.\n\n## Error to exit-code mapping\n\nThe CLI dispatcher translates engine error variants (and CLI-detected\npreconditions) to the exit-code classes above. This table binds each variant\nto its class.\n\n| Source error variant                             | Exit code | Class         |\n| ------------------------------------------------ | --------- | ------------- |\n| (clean completion)                               | 0         | success       |\n| recover sub-action gated by `--accept-data-loss` | 64        | data-loss-ack |\n| `doctor check-integrity` findings non-empty      | 65        | findings      |\n| `doctor safe-export` failed manifest/export step | 66        | artifact-fail |\n| `EngineError::Storage`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Projection`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Vector`                            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Embedder`                          | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Scheduler`                         | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::OpStore`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::Overloaded`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::SchemaValidation`                  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::WriteValidation`                   | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::EmbedderNotConfigured`             | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::KindNotVectorIndexed`              | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}`     | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::DatabaseLocked{..}`            | 71        | lock-held     |\n| `EngineError::Closing`                           | 71        | lock-held     |\n| `EngineOpenError::Corruption(..)`                | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::IncompatibleSchemaVersion{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::MigrationError{..}`            | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderIdentityMismatch{..}`  | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |\n| `EngineOpenError::Io{..}`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |\n\n## JSON output wrapping\n\n`fathomdb-cli` owns top-level discriminator wrapping. The engine returns\ntyped report structs; the CLI serializes them under a `verb` discriminator.\n\n- All `--json` output is one JSON object (or an NDJSON stream for `recover`).\n- Doctor verb wrapping pattern: `{ \"verb\": \"<verb-name>\", ...flattened_engine_report_fields... }`.\n- Non-flat reports nest naturally. For example, `IntegrityReport` serializes\n  as `{ \"verb\": \"check-integrity\", \"physical\": {...}, \"logical\": {...}, \"semantic\": {...} }`.\n- Field name policy: serde default `snake_case`. Any divergence from engine\n  field spellings lives in the CLI serialization layer; the engine report\n  structs are not renamed to satisfy CLI spelling requirements.\n","numLines":127,"startLine":1,"totalLines":127}}}
dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-20260517T210205Z.log:219:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0125TrwwLBocQeengvEi3J4p","type":"tool_result","content":"grep: requirements*.txt: No such file or directory\ngrep: pyproject.toml: No such file or directory\n---\nname: Release\n\non:\n  push:\n    tags:\n      - \"v*\"\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      dry_run:\n        description: \"Rehearse cargo --dry-run + npm --dry-run; PyPI publish + post-publish smoke skipped entirely (no test.pypi slot burn).\"\n        type: boolean\n        default: true\n\npermissions:\n  actions: read\n  contents: write\n  id-token: write\n\nenv:\n  DRY_RUN: ${{ inputs.dry_run || 'false' }}\n\njobs:\n  # Single ubuntu preflight. Combines:\n  #   - scripts/verify-release-gates.sh (tag↔Cargo.toml lockstep, set-version\n  #     --check-files lockstep, HEAD-on-main, CHANGELOG section, crate\n  #     publish metadata).\n  #   - actionlint on all workflow files (per feedback_workflow_validation —\n  #     yaml.safe_load passes schema-invalid syntax GitHub silently rejects).\n  verify-release:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    timeout-minutes: 10\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd # v6.0.2\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0  # need refs/heads/main for HEAD-reach check\n      - name: Install actionlint\n        run: |\n          curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rhysd/actionlint/v1.7.7/scripts/download-actionlint.bash \\\n            | bash -s -- 1.7.7\n          sudo mv actionlint /usr/local/bin/actionlint\n      - name: Validate workflow YAML\n        run: actionlint .github/workflows/*.yml\n      - name: Run release gates\n        # Runs on push (tag-format + version-axis enforced) and\n        # workflow_dispatch (tag check skipped, all other gates enforced;\n        # dispatch with dry_run=false emits an emergency-republish warning).\n        run: bash scripts/verify-release-gates.sh\n        env:\n          GH_TOKEN: ${{ github.token }}\n\n  # Multi-platform Python wheels via PyO3/maturin-action. Produces manylinux,\n  # macOS (x86_64 + arm64), and Windows wheels for Python 3.10-3.12. The\n  # working-directory must be `src/python` so maturin reads our pyproject.toml\n  # there (manifest-path = ../rust/crates/fathomdb-py/Cargo.toml).\n  build-python:\n    needs: verify-release\n    strategy:\n      fail-fast: false\n      matrix:\n        include:\n          - runner: ubuntu-latest\n            target: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\n            manylinux: \"2_28\"\n          - runner: ubuntu-latest\n            target: aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\n            manylinux: \"2_28\"\n          - runner: macos-latest\n            target: x86_64-apple-darwin\n          - runner: macos-latest\n            target: aarch64-apple-darwin\n          - runner: windows-latest\n            target: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc\n    runs-on: ${{ matrix.runner }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd # v6.0.2\n      - uses: actions/setup-python@a309ff8b426b58ec0e2a45f0f869d46889d02405 # v6.2.0\n        with:\n          python-version: \"3.11\"\n      - uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@3c5f7ea28cd621ae0bf5283f0e981fb97b8a7af9 # stable\n        with:","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c409cac9-fa4a-4d9f-9db5-55aae00050c6","uuid":"16c5b0e9-de22-4a98-8226-365dab147cd0","timestamp":"2026-05-17T21:02:33.649Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"grep: requirements*.txt: No such file or directory\ngrep: pyproject.toml: No such file or directory\n---\nname: Release\n\non:\n  push:\n    tags:\n      - \"v*\"\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      dry_run:\n        description: \"Rehearse cargo --dry-run + npm --dry-run; PyPI publish + post-publish smoke skipped entirely (no test.pypi slot burn).\"\n        type: boolean\n        default: true\n\npermissions:\n  actions: read\n  contents: write\n  id-token: write\n\nenv:\n  DRY_RUN: ${{ inputs.dry_run || 'false' }}\n\njobs:\n  # Single ubuntu preflight. Combines:\n  #   - scripts/verify-release-gates.sh (tag↔Cargo.toml lockstep, set-version\n  #     --check-files lockstep, HEAD-on-main, CHANGELOG section, crate\n  #     publish metadata).\n  #   - actionlint on all workflow files (per feedback_workflow_validation —\n  #     yaml.safe_load passes schema-invalid syntax GitHub silently rejects).\n  verify-release:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    timeout-minutes: 10\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd # v6.0.2\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0  # need refs/heads/main for HEAD-reach check\n      - name: Install actionlint\n        run: |\n          curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rhysd/actionlint/v1.7.7/scripts/download-actionlint.bash \\\n            | bash -s -- 1.7.7\n          sudo mv actionlint /usr/local/bin/actionlint\n      - name: Validate workflow YAML\n        run: actionlint .github/workflows/*.yml\n      - name: Run release gates\n        # Runs on push (tag-format + version-axis enforced) and\n        # workflow_dispatch (tag check skipped, all other gates enforced;\n        # dispatch with dry_run=false emits an emergency-republish warning).\n        run: bash scripts/verify-release-gates.sh\n        env:\n          GH_TOKEN: ${{ github.token }}\n\n  # Multi-platform Python wheels via PyO3/maturin-action. Produces manylinux,\n  # macOS (x86_64 + arm64), and Windows wheels for Python 3.10-3.12. The\n  # working-directory must be `src/python` so maturin reads our pyproject.toml\n  # there (manifest-path = ../rust/crates/fathomdb-py/Cargo.toml).\n  build-python:\n    needs: verify-release\n    strategy:\n      fail-fast: false\n      matrix:\n        include:\n          - runner: ubuntu-latest\n            target: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\n            manylinux: \"2_28\"\n          - runner: ubuntu-latest\n            target: aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu\n            manylinux: \"2_28\"\n          - runner: macos-latest\n            target: x86_64-apple-darwin\n          - runner: macos-latest\n            target: aarch64-apple-darwin\n          - runner: windows-latest\n            target: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc\n    runs-on: ${{ matrix.runner }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@de0fac2e4500dabe0009e67214ff5f5447ce83dd # v6.0.2\n      - uses: actions/setup-python@a309ff8b426b58ec0e2a45f0f869d46889d02405 # v6.2.0\n        with:\n          python-version: \"3.11\"\n      - uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@3c5f7ea28cd621ae0bf5283f0e981fb97b8a7af9 # stable\n        with:","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
