dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-planning-output.json:131:      "status": "CLOSED in fix-3 per HITL 2026-05-24. fix-1 had over-strictly closed this against the wrapper option (A), citing 'no new verbs' which is a paraphrase, not the literal § 54 contract ('no API breaks. Bugfix-only.'). Re-read of § 54 admits new methods as patch-safe additive surface. Four shapes re-evaluated: A wrapper return (type-checker friction, isinstance/pickling edge cases), B tuple return (rejected — breaks legacy), C new top-level verb `Engine.open_with_report` / `Engine.openWithReport` (clean but joins five-verb surface), D engine-attached accessor `engine.open_report()` / `engine.openReport()` (CHOSEN). Shape D rationale: zero risk to `Engine.open` (signature unchanged), clean types, slots into the existing engine-attached instrumentation taxonomy alongside `engine.counters()`, `engine.drain()`. Spec edits relocate the report from 'Runtime surface' to 'Engine-attached instrumentation / control' in both `dev/interfaces/python.md` and `dev/interfaces/typescript.md`. Idempotency contract: repeated calls return identical data captured at open time. Full rationale in `dev/plans/0.6.1-implementation.md` § 'Q-002 resolution (HITL 2026-05-24)'.",
dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-planning-output.json:139:      "options": "(a) yes — orchestrator spawns one-off WF-fix-style slice before AXIS-E-PIN | (b) no — log under 0.6.x patch chain follow-up",
dev/plans/runs/0.6.1-planning-output.json:152:        {"id": "F-2", "severity": "medium", "title": "Legacy Engine.open compatibility only partially pinned", "addressed_by": "fix-1 promoted legacy-callsite regression test to PRIMARY GATE and closed Q-002 against new verbs. fix-3 (HITL 2026-05-24) reopened Q-002 against the strict § 54 text ('no API breaks. Bugfix-only.'), evaluated four shapes, chose Shape D (engine-attached accessor `engine.open_report()` / `engine.openReport()`). `Engine.open` signature stays unchanged from 0.6.0; legacy compat is now structural, not test-only. OPENREPORT-py / OPENREPORT-ts skeletons + plan-doc slice-sequence rows + AC-068c/d wording updated for Shape D."}
