dev/plans/runs/11c-fix-1-20260516T225956Z.log:76:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VevdXxopypTem8AuKg2Dsd","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Phase 11c Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n2\t\n3\tReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\n4\tTarget: branch `phase-11c-set-version-20260516T221655Z` HEAD `d408361`.\n5\tBaseline: `1404bf2` on `0.6.0-rewrite`.\n6\tCherry-pick: `7c1391c` / `2e5f00d` / `e1465d9` / `d5bff2b` on\n7\t`0.6.0-rewrite`.\n8\tReview log: `dev/plans/runs/11c-review-20260516T223403Z.log`.\n9\t\n10\tSandbox note: reviewer could not write this file directly (read-only\n11\tsandbox). Main thread promoted the verbatim verdict from log line\n12\t2604+.\n13\t\n14\t## Verdict: BLOCK\n15\t\n16\t### 1. [high] AC-051a under-covered — fixture is a direct pin, not sibling transitive skew\n17\t\n18\tRefs:\n19\t\n20\t- `dev/release/fixtures/cargo-skew/Cargo.toml:18`\n21\t- `dev/release/tests/cargo_skew.sh:24`\n22\t- `dev/acceptance.md:823`\n23\t\n24\tThe acceptance text requires a fixture where `fathomdb = X` and\n25\t`fathomdb-embedder = Y` pull incompatible transitive\n26\t`fathomdb-embedder-api` ranges, but the landed fixture only creates\n27\ta single direct dependency on `fathomdb-embedder-api = \"=99.99.99\"`.\n28\tThat proves Cargo rejects an impossible direct pin; it does not\n29\tprove sibling-package skew is detected in the real release shape.\n30\t\n31\t### 2. [medium] `--check-files` diagnostics weaker than contract\n32\t\n33\tRefs:\n34\t\n35\t- `scripts/set-version.sh:202`\n36\t- `scripts/set-version.sh:207`\n37\t- `scripts/set-version.sh:213`\n38\t- `scripts/set-version.sh:243`\n39\t- `scripts/set-version.sh:247`\n40\t- `scripts/tests/test_set_version.sh:136`\n41\t\n42\tThe prompt requires one drift line per mismatch with `file:line`\n43\tplus observed/expected values, but the script emits only file paths\n44\tand messages, and the test suite only checks that the filename\n45\tappears.\n46\t\n47\t### 3. [low] `output.json` stale relative to slice HEAD\n48\t\n49\tRefs:\n50\t\n51\t- `dev/plans/runs/11c-set-version-output.json:5`\n52\t- `dev/plans/runs/11c-set-version-output.json:27`\n53\t\n54\t`output.json` records `head_sha` as `3cf95ca` and omits the final\n55\tdocs commit, even though the reviewed head is `d408361`. Since this\n56\tfile exists to capture closure state, it should be regenerated.\n57\t\n58\t## What passed on inspection\n59\t\n60\t- Axis E decoupling is present.\n61\t- The workspace comment cites `dev/design/release.md`.\n62\t- `scripts/hooks/pre-push` runs `scripts/set-version.sh --check-files`\n63\t  before `agent-verify.sh`.\n64\t- The pip-skew fixture documents the synthetic-package rationale in\n65\t  `output.json`.\n66\t- `scripts/agent-test.sh` wires the new tests into the agent test\n67\t  loop.\n68\t\n69\t## Reviewer process notes\n70\t\n71\t- Reviewer could not write the verdict file directly (read-only\n72\t  sandbox); main thread promoted from log.\n73\t- Reviewer could not rerun write-heavy commands (cargo check,\n74\t  agent-verify); pass claims for those rely on the checked-in\n75\t  artifact plus code inspection. Main thread independently verified\n76\t  cargo check + set-version test + set-version --check-files all\n77\t  green on `0.6.0-rewrite` after cherry-pick.\n78\t\n79\t## Orchestrator triage\n80\t\n81\t- Finding 1 = real AC binding gap. The current cargo-skew fixture\n82\t  is symmetric in shape to the pip-skew problem (no published\n83\t  packages mean transitive sibling skew can't be exercised against\n84\t  the real release names). Same solution applies: build synthetic\n85\t  mock-skew-a + mock-skew-b crates (analogues to pip-skew's\n86\t  `mock-skew-api` + `probe-a` / `probe-b`) that declare conflicting\n87\t  ranges on a shared synthetic api crate. Document the\n88\t  real-name swap as part of REQ-048 publishing landing.\n89\t- Finding 2 = mechanical. Each drift-emit site adds `file:line` +\n90\t  observed + expected values. ~15 LOC patch. Update the test suite\n91\t  assertions to match.\n92\t- Finding 3 = regenerate output.json with the correct head_sha and\n93\t  the post-fix commit list.\n94\t\n95\tRecommendation: spawn 11c-fix-1 remediation pass (Opus 4.7 medium).\n96\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b342a0e-c53a-4ac0-8364-0acbe4d45977","uuid":"34575c71-b49f-4682-ab5a-6dfe75108428","timestamp":"2026-05-16T23:00:05.138Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/dev/plans/runs/11c-review-20260516T223403Z.md","content":"# Phase 11c Review — codex gpt-5.4 verdict\n\nReviewer: `codex --model gpt-5.4 --sandbox read-only`.\nTarget: branch `phase-11c-set-version-20260516T221655Z` HEAD `d408361`.\nBaseline: `1404bf2` on `0.6.0-rewrite`.\nCherry-pick: `7c1391c` / `2e5f00d` / `e1465d9` / `d5bff2b` on\n`0.6.0-rewrite`.\nReview log: `dev/plans/runs/11c-review-20260516T223403Z.log`.\n\nSandbox note: reviewer could not write this file directly (read-only\nsandbox). Main thread promoted the verbatim verdict from log line\n2604+.\n\n## Verdict: BLOCK\n\n### 1. [high] AC-051a under-covered — fixture is a direct pin, not sibling transitive skew\n\nRefs:\n\n- `dev/release/fixtures/cargo-skew/Cargo.toml:18`\n- `dev/release/tests/cargo_skew.sh:24`\n- `dev/acceptance.md:823`\n\nThe acceptance text requires a fixture where `fathomdb = X` and\n`fathomdb-embedder = Y` pull incompatible transitive\n`fathomdb-embedder-api` ranges, but the landed fixture only creates\na single direct dependency on `fathomdb-embedder-api = \"=99.99.99\"`.\nThat proves Cargo rejects an impossible direct pin; it does not\nprove sibling-package skew is detected in the real release shape.\n\n### 2. [medium] `--check-files` diagnostics weaker than contract\n\nRefs:\n\n- `scripts/set-version.sh:202`\n- `scripts/set-version.sh:207`\n- `scripts/set-version.sh:213`\n- `scripts/set-version.sh:243`\n- `scripts/set-version.sh:247`\n- `scripts/tests/test_set_version.sh:136`